10 minutes in, I knew I would never not buy this game.

Completion time: 10 hours of me booking it left me with the main story finished and a 75% completion rating (loading the save file lets you continue as normal). Probably going to log another ~5 hours before I'm 100%.

Worth it? I bought it on sale for $23, but if I had bought it for the full $30, I'd still say it's worth the money. Regardless of how much time I'll get out of it (although 10+ is nothing to scoff at), I thoroughly enjoyed myself and years from now will remember this one with a positive sense of nostalgia.

Pros:
+characters that, for all their simplicity, I just couldn't get enough of;
+charming voice acting that keeps with the game's aesthetic (there is also an option unlockable early on in the game to have characters mumble instead of talk, Legend-of-Zelda-style, if that's your thing);
+a slew of little details in the world that'll make you smile (playing pattycake with a random Mafia guy before he *****slaps you off a building);
+every boss fight has interesting mechanics that you have to get used to;
+diverse level design (even when you get the basic gameplay mechanics down, the levels all play differently from each other, and the worlds are definitely unique);
+gameplay that doesn't tire easily;
+and a great soundtrack that feeds right into the atmosphere of each location.

Cons:
-It ends. T-T +(But you can revisit all previous levels easy-peasy.)

